'Gracious and smart' Melania skips first night of Republican convention
content: ​Former first lady Melania Trump did not turn up at the first night of the Republican National Convention Monday while Trump made a triumphant entry some 48 hours after the assassination bid. Model and influencer Amber Rose, however, mentioned Melania on the stage as she recounted a meeting with Melania and Donald Trump. “The first lady was gracious and smart, with a smile that will brighten up any room," Amber Rose said.

content: Vice President Kamala Harris left a congratulatory voicemail to GOP Ohio Senator JD Vance on Monday after he was announced as the Republican vice presidential pick on Truth Social by former President Donald Trump.

title: Pakistan govt raises petrol by PKR 9.99, diesel by PKR 6.18 due to global market pressures
content: According to a notification from the Finance Division, petrol prices surged by PKR 9.99 per litre, reaching PKR 275.6/ltr, while HSD saw a rise of PKR 6.18/ltr, settling at PKR 283.63/ltr for the upcoming fortnight.

'Used to watch Bengals games': What Vivek Ramaswamy said about Trump's VP pick JD Vance
content: Vivek Ramaswamy has publicly endorsed Donald Trump's choice of JD Vance as his running mate for the forthcoming US presidential elections. Ramaswamy, who attended law school with Vance, fondly recalled their time together watching Bengals games at the bar and expressed amazement at their progress over the past ten years.

Elon Musk to give $45 million a month to pro-Trump super PAC
content: Elon Musk has committed to contributing $45 million per month to a pro-Donald Trump political group, significantly boosting the Republican nominee's reelection campaign finances through the November election. This substantial financial support aims to enhance Trump's fundraising advantage over President Joe Biden, who has recently faced a donor revolt and calls for a new nominee.
